# POL address hygiene

When editing POL addresses or published contract data:

## Layers (names must match across all four)

1. `contracts-internal/script/pol/POLAddresses.sol` — struct fields + mainnet/bepolia literals
2. `data/pol-addresses-mapping.json` — `published`, `contractsPath`, `polField`
3. `data/contracts.json` — site addresses
4. `make contracts-generate` — snippets + deployed-contract pages (do not hand-edit generated output)

## Required checks

```bash
make check-pol-addresses        # ok / not_ok summary; fails if not_ok > 0 (included in make check)
make list-pol-addresses-not-ok  # human list of not_ok rows
```

`not_ok` means action required (`address_changed`, `missing_in_contracts_json`, `publish_undecided`, mapping errors). `not_published` is intentional omission — not a failure.

## Fix loop

- Drift or missing docs row → `data/contracts.json` → `make contracts-generate` → commit generated files
- Undecided publish → set `published: false` or complete mapping + json for `published: true`
- Struct/literal/mapping mismatch → fix `POLAddresses.sol` and mapping together

Status definitions: `scripts/contracts/verify-pol-addresses.mjs` file header. Contributor guide: `CONTRIBUTING.md` §7.
